          <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">men</ENAMEX> donated <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">blood</ENAMEX>, which was analyzed from <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1994</TIMEX> through
          <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1995</TIMEX>. <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">Two</NUMEX>-<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">hundred and forty</NUMEX>-<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">women</ENAMEX> who donated
          blood had <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">children</ENAMEX> and <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">153</NUMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">men</ENAMEX> had <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">children</ENAMEX>. We
          searched for birth certificates of self-reported
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">children</ENAMEX>. If either the birth certificate or the mother
